{
  "doc_id": "6033",
  "text": "Firstly, variations of a specific functional unit may be available. This means, for example, that optimized versions regarding chip size, latency, and throughput are available for a functional unit. The most appropriate implementation is chosen dynamically at runtime and may change throughout the lifetime of the application. The AMIDAR model allows the processor to adapt to the actual workload by substitution of two versions of a functional unit at runtime. In [CITATION_1] , we have shown that the characteristics of the functional units can be changed to optimally suit the needs of the running application.",
  "correct_citation": {
